@Database Changes_To_V1.04.guide

@Node Main "Changes to HydraBBS between V1.03 and V1.04"

  *** Sysop Information ***

  Please read *ALL* of this file, or you won't know about some of the great
  new features of this release.

  Go on, it'll only take you a couple of minutes.

  This document is stored as HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/Changes_To_V1.04.Guide


  Changes to HydraBBS between V1.03 and V1.04
  ===========================================

  * Tools!

    If you look in HBBS:System/Amiga/CLI you will now find the
    tools that I used in the default "FileID" config file that are
    used to extract and update file id's.

    I also recommend the following versions of these archivers:

    LhA 2.1 (04/17/99)
    LZX 1.20
    UnZip 5.32 of 3 November 1997, by Info-ZIP
    DMS 1.53 Turbo Pro, Updated 1993 by Blackhawk/PARADOX

    (Any later versions should be fine, but make sure you test them,
    also note that some versions of UnZip are case sensitive and require
    options to make them case insensitive)

    All the tools I use can be obtained from Aminet.

  * Example Config Files

    ** IMPORTANT ***

    Oops, the example config called HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/System/FileID
    was telling LHA and LZX to use a temporary directory of ":T" still

    But I didn't mention this in the docs, lha and lzx may not have been able to
    update file_id.diz's in some files if you didn't have a "T" directory
    in the root of the partition that HydraBBS was installed on.

    I have removed the "-w:T" paramaters from the example config now, please
    check to see if this is required or incorrect for your system.

    Setting the -w option for LHA and LZX (or other archivers that have to update
    very large archives) is a GOOD THING if you have a file bigger than your
    available memory.  See the docs for LHA and LZX for more about what the -w
    option does.

  * ExtractDIZ

    Internally changed to use HBBS_DosCommand() instead of HBBS_RunDOSCMD()

    ** IMPORTANT **

    Please modify your "HBBS:System/FileID" file and remove all occurences
    of "<>NIL:" as the output from these commands is now handled by
    the system.

  * Adverts

    Created this new system door, it's used to add adverts to files
    based on file types.

    The config file is *very* similar to the HBBS:System/FCheck config
    file.  This door was requested by [-SPY-].

    Please see @{"HBBS:Docs/Doors/Adverts.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/Adverts.Guide/MAIN}

  * Check_Corrupt

    Created door, please see @{"HBBS:Docs/Doors/Check_Corrupt.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/Check_Corrupt.Guide/MAIN}

    HBBS:System/FileID is completely different now. see the docs.

  * FreeDL

    This door has been created, please see @{"HBBS:Docs/Doors/FreeDL.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/FreeDL.Guide/MAIN}

  * AskConf

    Updated so that you can configure the messages displayed to a user from
    a config file.  Please see @{"HBBS:Docs/Doors/AskConf.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/AskConf.Guide/MAIN}

  * Node

    The LastCallers/PWFails/Pagers etc display in the info window
    (and thus, the same data in the Control area) is now time and date-stamped.

    If the user is kicked off by the sysop (via SHIFT+F10 when they're online)
    the callers log will now have a message in it tho this effect.

    Also a new action character will be added to the callers log actions
    log: "K".

  * XPR

    Fixed the hanging of a node window when you cancel an XPR
    transfer, also, when you cancel an XPR transfer now, the other
    computer (i.e. the user's machine) receives the cancel message
    properly.  All this happens because of an undocumented XPR
    library feature!  Great...

    Well now I've tested cancelling an xfer before the user actually
    started receving and it doesn't lock up the node or crash it now.
    tested using nullmodem.device and telnetd.device. both were OK..

    However, when a user attempts to cancel the transfer it does not
    regognise or acknoledge the cancel request, the xpr window
    just sits there until the XPR transfer times out..

    For your information, because the XPR and Hydra transfer doors
    are external, they must use the already opened serial device
    that is on-line, without using SERF_SHARED (because some devices
    do not support that mode of working), the problem with it has
    been releasing the serial device BACK to the node program.  I
    think this is fixed now but it needs more people to test it and
    let me know that it's working OK.

    So please, if it works now and it didn't before then please let me
    know what serial.device driver you're using..

    The HYDRA door used an alternate method of grabbing the serial
    port, which I've now implemented into the XPR door.

  * MoveFile

    It would never actually move a BAD file to the Conference's BADFiles
    directory - fixed.

    It was displayed "file moved to download path" even when the file had been
    moved to a HOLD or BAD etc directory, now it just displays "File moved OK"

    If anyone wants this door to tell the USER where the file was moved to then
    let me know and I'll add it in (very simple)

  * CheckFiles

    Adjusted calling of Check_Corrupt system door, paramaters
    re-organized and changed.  Existing doors will have to be re-coded

    Now calls an "Adverts" system door at the request of [-SPY-]

    Added extensive carrier loss checking, things were being written to the
    screen after a user dropped carrier during a file check.

    Added NOSYSOPTEXT system option, use in HBBS:Commands/System if you like..
    This limits checkfile's output of the current file check progress to
    the sysop.

    See the example config file, HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System

  * FileLister

    Added option to scan the BADFILES list for a conference.

    Type in "FR ?" at the command prompt

  * Download

    Now checks if the tagged files are valid for sysop downloads
    (usefull if you tag files in a cd-rom conference and have a
    different or no cd in the drive)

  * HBBSNode.library and HBBSCommon.library

    Libversion and Librevision were accidentally set to 17.2!

    Librevision CANNOT be set to ".04", so it'll be set to "0"
    until "V1.10".

    This only affects the version command when the library is
    in memory, as the actual $VER: string is correct, i.e. "V1.04",
    Fortunatly this is what most things use...

  * HBBSCommon.library

    Added HBBS_DosCommand().  Similar to HBBS_RunDOSCMD() except that
    it accepts flags instead of a single paramater.  You can use it
    with RDC_#? flags in defines.h.

    See HBBS:Developer/Docs/hbbscommon.library.doc for details.

  * FileHistory

    Removed SysopText()'s and make it use HBBS_DosCommand() instead of
    HBBS_RunDOSCMD()

    Added "-x0" to the paramaters for LHA and LZX

  * CheckTags

    File tags were cleared at login if user had tagged files and they dropped
    carrier at the "Keep tagged files ?" prompt, fixed!

  * LastCallers

    Added an option NoScreenClear.  then the output file won't contain a
    screen clear, so you can add headers to it!

    For usage, just run "HBBS:Utils/LastCallers" with no paramaters.

  * Control

    Changed the "BBS Config" button to "BBSGlobal".  I might change this back
    when there's a GUI or alternate config file editor that can be specified.

  * XPR, Hydra, Node, AskDLFiles, CheckTags and Tag_File

    These programs/doors have been updated to cope with free downloads.

  * CmdPrompt

    Now writes to the callers log when the user runs out of time.

  * AddTime and AddCred

    Removed a couple of old DOOR_SysopText()'s

@EndNode
